abstract: Nour el Sherbini defeats Amanda Sobhy to win JP Morgan Tournament of Champions, annual international squash championship; Sobhy is first American-born player to reach final.

headline.print_headline: Sports Briefing | Squash; American Loses in Final
headline.main: Rising Squash Star Has Triumphant Week Despite Loss in Tournament Final

snippet: Amanda Sobhy, a Long Island native and Harvard graduate, finished second to Nour el Sherbini at the J.P. Morgan Tournament of Champions, but some believe she can reach No. 1 in the world rankings.
lead_paragraph: Amanda Sobhy, a Long Island native and Harvard graduate, finished second to Nour el Sherbini at the J.P. Morgan Tournament of Champions, but some believe she can reach No. 1 in the world rankings.
